 40,270<ref name=\"AC-2018\"/>\n| guests     = [[Patricia Acevedo]], Yuri Akiba, Akira, [[B-Project]], [[Beau Billingslea]], [[Mario Casta\u00f1eda]], Leon Chiro, Color Pointe, Dancing Dolls, Hana Dinh, Dorilooko, Shunsuke Hasegawa, Honey Popcorn, [[Doug Jones (actor)|Doug Jones]], [[Tetsuya Kakihara]], Pion Kim, [[Chiaki Kon]], Astarohime Koyu, Made Monster, Maul Cosplay, [[Yua Mikami]], Hideki Nakayama, Natsumi, Enji Night, Fumio Osano, Pugoffka, Root, Ryu-en, [[Asami Sanada]], DJ Shintaro, Shiva, Somenzari, DJ Sunamori, Mari Takahashi, Team China, Mirei Touyama, [[Hibiki Yoshizaki]], and [[Zwei (band)|Zwei]].<ref name=\"AC-2018\"/>\n}}\n{{Convention list\n| date       = June 13-16, 2019\n| venue      = George R. Brown Convention Center\n| location   = Houston, Texas\n| attendance = \n| guests     = [[Apink]], [[Eva Bella]], Ricardo Brust, [[Mario Casta\u00f1eda]], Leon Chiro, Richard Dorton, [[Rick Farmiloe]], Gacharic Spin, Hana Bunny, HaneAme, [[Wataru Hatano]], [[Junko Iwao]], Doug Jones, Ellen Kim, [[Aina Kusuda]], [[Patrick Kwok-Choon]], [[Ladybaby]], Reuben Langdon, Jason Liles, Made Monster, Alan Maxson, Vic Mignogna, DJ Misaki P, Sara Mitich, [[Nervo (DJs)|Nervo]], Enji Night, [[Nobuhiko Okamoto]], Reika, Damon Runyan, Harumo Sanazaki, [[Nozomu Sasaki]], [[T.J. Storm|TJ Storm]], and Livvy Stubenrauch.<ref name=\"AC-2019\"/>\n}}\n{{Convention list\n| date       = July 9-12, 2020\n| venue      = George R. Brown Convention Center\n| location   = Houston, Texas\n| attendance = \n| guests     = Ricardo Brust, [[James Callis]], [[Mario Casta\u00f1eda]], Hana Bunny, HaneAme, and Pugoffka.<ref name=\"AC-2020\"/>\n}}\n|}\n\n==Anime Matsuri Hawaii==\nAnime Matsuri Hawaii (AMHI) was a three-day anime convention held during November at the [[Hawaii Convention Center]] in [[Honolulu, Hawaii]].<ref name=ann03242015/> The convention's programming included a concert, cosplay showcase, J-Fashion show, screenings, and panels.<ref name=hsa11262015/> Yuegene Fay, a cosplayer, was unable to make a guest appearance due to immigration issues. Anime Matsuri Hawaii did not return in 2016.<ref name=hsa06062016/>\n\n===Event history===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"100%\"\n|-\n! Dates !! Location !! Atten. !! Guests\n{{Convention list\n| date       = November 27\u201329, 2015\n| venue      = [[Hawaii Convention Center]]\n| location   = [[Honolulu|Honolulu, Hawaii]]\n| attendance = \n| guests     = Johnny Yong Bosch, Stella Chuu, [[Daizystripper|DaizyStripper]], Maile Flanagan, Crispin Freeman, Goldy, Shunsuke Hasegawa, Linda Le, Yui Minakata, Masahiko Otsuka, Reika, Justin Rojas, and Chinatsu Taira.<ref name=\"AC-2015amhi\"/>\n}}\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|2|refs=\n\n<ref name=\"about2009\">{{cite news | url=http://manga.about.com/b/2009/04/07/this-weekend-sakura-con-anime-matsuri-and-kawaii-kon.htm | title = This Weekend: Sakura-Con, Anime Matsuri and Kawaii-Kon | work = [[About.com]] | date = 7 April 2009 | accessdate = February 3, 2013 | author = Aoki, Deb}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AC-2007\">{{cite web | url = https://animecons.com/events/info/1157/anime-matsuri-2007 | title = Anime Matsuri 2007 Information | publisher = AnimeCons.com | accessdate = 2016-01-07}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AC-2008\">{{cite web | url = https://animecons.com/events/info/1464/anime-matsuri-2008 | title = Anime Matsuri 2008 Information | publisher = AnimeCons.com | accessdate = 2016-01-07}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AC-2009\">{{cite web | url = https://animecons.com/events/info/1609/anime-matsuri-2009 | title = Anime Matsuri 2009 Information | publisher = AnimeCons.com | accessdate = 2016-01-07}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AC-2010\">{{cite web | url = https://animecons.com/events/info/1838/anime-matsuri-2010 | title = Anime Matsuri 2010 Information | publisher = AnimeCons.com | accessdate = 2016-01-07}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"AC-2011\">{{cite web | url = https://animecons.com/events/info/2203/anime-matsuri-2011 | title = Anime Matsuri 2011 Information | publisher = AnimeCons