m/2016/06/06/anime-matsuri-hawaii-cancels-2016-convention/|accessdate=28 May 2017|work=Honolulu Star Advertiser|date=June 6, 2016}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=japanator09>{{cite news|last1=Veron|first1=Red|title=Anime Matsuri '09: Child's Play Charity Auction|url=http://www.japanator.com/anime-matsuri-09-child-s-play-charity-auction-9673.phtml|accessdate=31 October 2014|work=Japanator|date=April 13, 2009}}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"khou2013\">{{cite web|title=Anime Matsuri Convention |publisher=[[KHOU-TV]] |url=http://events.khou.com/Anime_Matsuri_Convention/266900494.html |accessdate=2013-05-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131004215548/http://events.khou.com/Anime_Matsuri_Convention/266900494.html |archivedate=2013-10-04 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=\"khou2014\">{{cite web|title=Great Day Anime Matsuri |publisher=[[KHOU-TV]] |url=http://www.khou.com/great-day/gdh_3-6-14_seg5-248850001.html |accessdate=2014-04-17 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140419015931/http://www.khou.com/great-day/gdh_3-6-14_seg5-248850001.html |archivedate=2014-04-19 }}</ref>\n\n<ref name=nfanimematsuri2013>{{cite news|title=Anime Matsuri set to take over Houston|url=http://newsfixnow.com/2013/11/26/anime-matsuri-set-to-take-over-houston/|accessdate=18 April 2014|newspaper=KIAH-TV NewsFix}}</ref>\n\n}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{official website|animematsuri.com}}\n\n{{Anime conventions in North America}}\n{{Texas SF Conventions}}\n{{Houston |state=autocollapse}}\n\n{{coord|29|45|8|N|95|21|28|W|region:US-TX_type:event|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Anime conventions in the United States]]\n[[Category:Recurring events established in 2007]]\n[[Category:2007 establishments in Texas]]\n[[Category:Annual events in Texas]]\n[[Category:Conventions in Texas]]\n[[Category:Festivals in Houston]]\n[[Category:Tourist attractions in Houston]]\n", "text_old": "{{For|the anime convention in Ohio|Matsuricon}}\n{{Infobox Convention\n| name       = Anime Matsuri\n| image      = \n| caption    = \n| status     = Active\n| genre      = [[Anime]], Japanese culture<ref name=\"khou2013\"/><ref name=\"khou2014\"/>\n| venue      = [[George R. Brown Convention Center]]\n| location   = [[Houston, Texas]]\n| country    = United States\n| first      = 2007\n| attendance = 40,270 in 2018<ref name=\"AC-2018\"/>\n| organizer  = Deniece and John Leigh<ref name=\"hc03282018\"/>\n| events     = \n| website    = http://www.animematsuri.com/\n}}\n\n'''Anime Matsuri''' is an annual four-day [[anime convention]] traditionally held during spring at the [[George R. Brown Convention Center]] in [[Houston, Texas]]. The convention's name comes from the Japanese word '[[matsuri]]' meaning festival.<ref name=houstonia03312015/> \n\n==Programming==\nThe convention's programming includes an artists' alley, a carshow, the attendance of celebrities and special guests, [[cosplay]] chess, cosplay contests, fashion shows, gaming events, karaoke, [[LARP]], live concerts, maid cafe, panels, a vendors' and exhibitors' area, and workshops.<ref name=\"khou2013\"/><ref name=\"hp130402\"/><ref name=hp03132014/><ref name=fph03182014/><ref name=hp03302015/><ref name=\"cw04072017\"/> The Charity Auction benefited Child's Play in 2009 and raised over $3,000.<ref name=japanator09/>\n\n==History==\nThe convention was held at [[George R. Brown Convention Center]] and Hilton Americas in 2007.<ref name=\"AC-2007\"/> Anime Matsuris 2008, 2009, 2010, and 2012 were held at the Woodlands Waterway Marriott Hotel and Convention Center, and Anime Matsuri 2011 was held at the Crowne Plaza Houston Hotel near [[Reliant Park]]/Medical Center.<ref name=\"AC-2008\" /><ref name=\"AC-2011\" /> Anime Matsuri 2013 was held at [[Hyatt Regency Houston]].<ref name=\"AC-2013\" /> The [[Syfy]] reality series ''[[Heroes of Cosplay]]'' filmed the masquerade at Anime Matsuri and was featured in an episode.<ref name=\"ann2013heroesofcosplay\"/> The convention in 2014 moved to the George R. Brown Convention Center.<ref name=hp03132014/><ref name=nfanimematsuri2013/> Complaints about the 2014 convention included long lines and delays.<ref name=fph03182014/> Despite the issues, the 2014 convention became the 9th largest North American anime convention.<ref name=\"aclargest2014\"/> The convention in 2015 remained at the George R. Brown Convention Center and used the first and most of the second floors.<ref name=hp03302015/><ref name=hc04042015/> The 2015 convention became the 8th largest North American anime convention.<ref name=\"aclargest2015\"/>\n\n==Controversies==\n\n=== Failure to pay guests and provide services ===\nOwners of Anime Matsuri have a history of not paying guests like Japanese artists, [[BESPA KUMAMERO]] in 2008, [[Miyavi]] in 2009,<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.houstonpress.com/arts/the-con-anime-matsuri-is-growing-and-so-is-the-list-of-people-unhappy-with-it-7764398|title=The Con: Anime Matsuri Is Growing, and so Is the List of People Unhappy With It|last=Rouner|first=Jef|date=2015-09-15|website=Houston Press|access-date=2019-06-19}}</ref>  [[Flow (Japanese band)|Flow]] in 2012, and [[Nightmare (Japanese band)|Nightmare]] in 2014. Nightmare's show began late due to poor planning by Anime Matsuri's staff and even released song about John Leigh with \"SUPER BOOGER MAN\" on their \"Taboo\" single on June 25, 2014, a few months after performing at convention.\n\nThey also did not provide food or translators for guest cosplayers like Midori and Akira during their fan signing in 2014. The guests had to ask fans for food in Japanese for a hamburger and were grateful to the fans who helped them.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://lineblog.me/akiriot/archives/1002188.html|title=\u30b5\u30a4\u30f3\u4f1a|website=AKIRA \u516c\u5f0f\u30d6\u30ed\u30b0|language=ja|access-date=2019-06-19}}</ref>\n\n=== Sexual harassment ===\nAfter Anime Matsuri 2015, John Leigh, the conventions event manager was accused of sexual harassment by several members of the [[Lolita fashion]] community.<ref name=\"hp06292015\" /> Significant financial improprieties have also been alleged against the convention organizers.<ref name=\"hp09152015\" /> In May 2016, Anime Matsuri announced that the former CEO of [[Anime Expo]], Marc Perez would join the convention as COO.<ref name=\"ann2016perez\" /><ref name=\"acperez2016\" /> The convention sent Tyler Willis, owner of YouTube channel Last Week Lolita News a cease and desist letter in early 2018 after reporting about John Leigh's sexual harassment.<ref name=\"af01092018\" /><ref name=\"cb02222018\" /> Boycott Anime Matsuri was formed in 2018 to inform about the conventions past actions, with guests such as [[Johnny Yong Bosch]], ''[[Steven Universe]]'' voice actors, and [[FEMM (duo)|Femm]] later canceling.<ref name=\"hc03282018\" /><ref name=\"cb02222018\" /> Leigh also apologized for his past actions.<ref name=\"hc03282018\" />\n\n==Event history==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" width=\"100%\"\n|-\n! Dates !! Location !! Atten. !! Guests\n{{Convention list\n| date       = April 27\u201329, 2007\n| venue      = [[George R. Brown Convention Center]]<br/>& Hilton Americas\n| location   = [[Houston, Texas]]\n| attendance = 4,012<ref name=\"AC-2007\"/>\n| guests     = [[Christine Auten]], [[Christopher Ayres]], [[Back-On]], [[Jessica Boone]], [[Peter Cullen]], Fizz, [[Tiffany Grant]], [[Matt Greenfield]], [[Hilary Haag]], [[Yaya Han]], Kyle Jones, [[Chris Patton]], RikkuX, and [[John Swasey]].<ref name=\"AC-2007\"/>\n}}\n{{Convention list\n| date       = March 21\u201323, 2008\n| venue      = The Woodlands Waterway Marriott Hotel<br/>& Convention Center\n| location   = [[The Woodlands, Texas]]\n| attendance = 5,993<ref name=\"AC-2008\"/>\n| guests     = [[Aural Vampire]], Amelie Belcher, Bespa Kumamero, [[Luci Christian]], JoEllen Elam, Yaya Han, [[Kate Higgins]], [[Yuri Lowenthal]], [[Matthew Mercer]], [[Vic Mignogna]], [[Tara Platt]], [[Patrick Seitz]], [[Stephanie Sheh]], Sky Pirate, Space Invader, Barbara Staples, [[Sonny Strait]], Bill Winans, and [[Stephanie Young]].<ref name=\"AC-2008\"/>\n}}\n{{Convention list\n| date       = April 10\u201312, 2009\n| venue      = The Woodlands Waterway Marriott Hotel<br/>& Convention Center\n| location   = The Woodlands, Texas\n| attendance = 6,950<ref name=\"AC-2009\"/>\n| guests     = Takuya Angel, [[Clint Bickham]], Luci Christian, JoEllen Elam, [[Quinton Flynn]], [[Jason David Frank]], [[Crispin Freeman]], Gren, [[DJ Heavygrinder]], [[Mike McFarland]], Matthew Mercer, [[Misako Rocks!]], [[Miyavi]], Chris Patton, [[Cynthia Rothrock]], [[Kristine Sa]], [[Blake Shepard]], Sonny Strait, [[Mao Murakami|Strong Machine 2]], Diana Tolin, and Stephanie Young.<ref name=\"AC-2009\"/><ref name=\"about2009\"/>\n}}\n{{Convention list\n| date       = April 2\u20134, 2010\n| venue      = The Woodlands Waterway Marriott Hotel<br/>& Convention Center\n| location   = The Woodlands, Texas\n| attendance = 7,113<ref name=\"AC-2010\"/>\n| guests     = Aural Vampire, Back-On, [[Leah Clark]], [[Francesca Dani]], India Davis, Crispin Freeman, DJ Heavygrinder, Thais Jussim, Reuben Langdon, Elizabeth Licata, Mike McFarland, Matthew Mercer, and Strong Machine 2.<ref name=\"AC-2010\"/>\n}}\n{{Convention list\n| date       = March 18\u201320, 2011\n| venue      = Crowne Plaza Houston Hotel near<br/>Reliant Park / Medical Center\n| location   = Houston, Texas\n| attendance = 7,982<ref name=\"AC-2011\"/>\n| guests     = Luci Christian, [[Gacharic Spin]], [[Hamutsun Serve]], [[Hangry & Angry]], [[Kyle Hebert]], Mike McFarland, Matthew Mercer, Reni Mimura, [[Christopher Corey Smith|Christopher Smith]], Michael Suarez, [[J. Michael Tatum]], and Stephanie Young.<ref name=\"AC-2011\"/>\n}}\n{{Convention list\n| date       = April 6\u20138, 2012\n| venue      = The Woodlands Waterway Marriott Hotel<br/>& Convention Center\n| location   = The Woodlands, Texas\n| attendance = 10,422<ref name=\"AC-2012\"/>\n| guests     = Airship Isabella, [[Troy Baker]], Clint Bickham, Luci Christian, [[Maile Flanagan]], [[Flow (Japanese band)|Flow]], Kathryn \"Rynn\" Griffin, Yaya Han, DJ Heavygrinder, Akinori Isobe, Masumi Kano, Cyril Lumboy, Mike McFarland, Matthew Mercer, Vic Mignogna, [[Amy Reeder|Amy Reeder Hadley]], Sleeping Samurai, Strong Machine 2, [[Alexis Tipton]], [[Shinichi Watanabe]], Bill Winans, and Stephanie Young.<ref name=\"AC-2012\"/>\n}}\n{{Convention list\n| date       = March 29\u201331, 2013\n| venue      = [[Hyatt Regency Houston]]\n| location   = Houston, Texas\n| attendance = 14,989<ref name=\"AC-2013\"/>\n| guests     = [[Misako Aoki]], [[Johnny Yong Bosch]], David Brehm, [[Erin Fitzgerald]], Kathryn \"Rynn\" Griffin, Yaya Han, Kyle Hebert, [[Kelly Hu]], Catherine Jones, Masumi Kano, Mike McFarland, Matthew Mercer, [[Carli Mosier]], Justin Rojas, [[Michelle Rojas]], [[Janet Varney]], [[Waveya]], Bill Winans, and Stephanie Young.<ref name=\"AC-2013\"/>\n}}\n{{Convention list\n| date       = March 14\u201316, 2014\n| venue      = George R. Brown Convention Center\n| location   = Houston, Texas\n| attendance = 19,412<ref name=\"AC-2014\"/>\n| guests     = Misako Aoki, Johnny Yong Bosch, Luci Christian, Eyeshine, [[Caitlin Glass]], Shunsuke Hasegawa, DJ HeavyGrinder, Aya Ikeda, Catherine Jones, Masumi Kano, [[Linda Le]], Yuri Lowenthal, Mike McFarland, Matthew Mercer, Tara Platt, Marisha Ray, Reika, TeddyLoid, Janet Varney, Bill Winans, Mai Yamamoto, and Stephanie Young.<ref name=\"AC-2014\"/>\n}}\n{{Convention list\n| date       = April 3\u20135, 2015\n| venue      = George R. Brown Convention Center\n| location   = Houston, Texas\n| attendance = 24,328<ref name=\"AC-2015\"/>\n| guests     =  Misako Aoki, Asuka, Luci Christian, Olivia Chubear, Stella Chuu, Crispin Freeman, [[Todd Haberkorn]], Shunsuke Hasegawa, DJ HeavyGrinder, Catherine Jones, Shigeto Koyama, Harrison Krix, Linda Le, Maki, Michiyo Murase, Atsushi Nishigori, [[Nylon Pink]], Putumayo, Reika, Stephanie Sheh, Kaname Shiroboshi, Sushio, TeddyLoid, [[Anna Tsuchiya]], Hiromi